<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Virgin1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Virgin,</orth> subst. a maiden, a woman who has no knowledge of man: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.295" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 295</bibl> -- <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.295" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 295</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 133</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 133</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 133</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.119" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.178" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.186" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.127" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 127</bibl>. Used of any young woman not yet married: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.447" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 447</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.123" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.123" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 123</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.103" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.172" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 141</bibl>.<lb />Adjectively, == 1) pertaining to a maiden: <cit><quote>the general of hot desire was sleeping by a v. hand disarmed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 154.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 154, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this v. palm now kissing thine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.816" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 816</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the v. tribute paid by howling Troy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 56</bibl></cit> (== the tribute of a virgin). <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.255" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 255</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 5, 12</bibl>. 2) pure, chaste: <cit><quote>break her v. knot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 15</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 160</bibl>. <cit><quote>the white cold v. snow upon my heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 55</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy v. knight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>withering on the v. thorn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 77</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 77</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.323" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 323</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>